
COMPILING
=========

We are using Java 7

It currently requires following three Web Request Handler API projects to be built first, until the patches find their way back to their main repositories. 

$ git clone git@github.com:bblfish/wymiwyg-wrhapi.git
$ cd wymiwyg-wrhapi.git
$ mvn clean install -Dgpg.skip=true 

$ git clone git@github.com:bblfish/wymiwyg-wrhapi-osgi.git
$ cd wymiwyg-wrhapi-osgi
$ mvn clean install -Dgpg.skip=true 

$ git clone git@github.com:bblfish/wymiwyg-wrhapi-jetty.git
$ cd wymiwyg-wrhapi-jetty
$ mvn clean install -Dgpg.skip=true -Dmaven.test.skip=true

Once those are compiled download this git repository

$ cd parent
$ export MAVEN_OPTS='-Xmx512m -XX:-UseSplitVerifier' 
$ mvn clean install -Dmaven.test.skip=true

RUNNING
=======

You can then change into one of the platform.launcher.{tdb,sesame,mulgara} directories 

$ mkdir run
$ cd run
$ java -XX:-UseSplitVerifier -Xmx512m -Xdebug -Xrunjdwp:transport=dt_socket,server=y,suspend=n,address=5005 -Dorg.ops4j.pax.url.mvn.localRepository=/Volumes/Dev/hjs/.m2/repository -XX:MaxPermSize=248M -Dfile.encoding=utf-8 -jar ../target/platform.launcher.tdb-0.5-incubating-SNAPSHOT.jar --https_keystore_clientauth want  --https_port 8443 --https_keystore_path /Users/hjs/tmp/cert/KEYSTORE.jks --https_keystore_password secret

The above will start a https://webid.info/ enabled clerezza on port 8443 

